Due to the wavelike nature of phonons, their interaction with periodic perturbations leads to diffraction conditions which depend on the wavelength of the phonon and the spacing of the perturbations. We now consider the case of linear defects parallel to the z-axis periodically spaced by a distance D. The x and y coordinates of the defects are7x=0,y=jD(j=0,±1,±2,…).\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
